        img: "https://images.weedmaps.com/dispensaries/000/386/834/avatar/1776992111-400x400.png",
        google: { rating: 4.9, review_count: 479, maps_url: 'https://maps.google.com/?cid=5889851026020320896&g_mp=CiVnb29nbGUubWFwcy5wbGFjZXMudjEuUGxhY2VzLkdldFBsYWNlEAIYBCAA', reviews: [{author: 'Kimberly Grutzik', rating: 5, text: 'Peter & Brandon were super helpful today.  They took time to explain products, answered questions about the Farm bill and made me feel welcome in the shop.  Beautiful displays!', time: 'a month ago'}, {author: 'Pamiangeliz Santiago Arizola', rating: 5, text: 'I came out here on a work trip and found the only dispensary open until 10pm which was great with the long hours I work. Connor helped me out along with a very sweet girl who I didn’t get her name. Everyone was lovely and very welcoming. Quickly to help me! Only place with karts so expect to pay a little more and it’s valid. Worth the trip!', time: '3 months ago'}, {author: 'Beezy', rating: 5, text: 'Sweetleaves is legit! Clean showroom and helpful staff. Got lucky and came in right when they started selling the vapes/carts! 10/10 recommend!', time: '3 months ago'}, {author: 'Rachel Lochmann', rating: 5, text: 'ATM inside for cash. Solid service and variety of products. Got broken device once and they let me exchange no problem. Call ahead about flower, they might be out. Otherwise, 1g carts for ~$100, 1/2g for ~$50 An 8th of flower was $80, which is high, but it’s good quality and grown in state which is the current requirement by law. Packaging was cute too!', time: 'a month ago'}, {author: 'Robert Ruiz Sanchez', rating: 4, text: 'Sweet Leaves is hands down one of the most welcoming dispensaries I’ve visited. From the moment you walk in, the staff is genuinely friendly, knowledgeable, and happy to help without ever making you feel rushed. They take the time to answer questions and make great recommendations, which makes the whole experience enjoyable and stress-free.  Their selection of flower is outstanding—fresh, high qua', time: '3 months ago'}] }
